  'add-client': "# Add Client\n\nUse this to register a new rental client. Their details and licence photos are saved securely.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. Tap **Add Client** from the home screen.\n2. Fill in the client's details:\n   - First Name and Last Name (required)\n   - Date of Birth\n   - Address\n   - Licence Number (required)\n3. Tap **Next — Scan Licence**.\n4. **Licence Front** — point the camera at the front of the licence and tap **Capture Photo**. Review the image and tap **Use This Photo** or **Retake**.\n5. **Licence Back** — repeat for the back of the licence.\n6. Review both images on the confirmation screen.\n7. Tap **Save Client** to submit.\n\n## Notes\n\n- First Name, Last Name, and Licence Number are required before you can proceed to the camera step.\n- Hold the licence flat, in good light, and fill the frame for a clear scan.\n- Once saved, the client record and licence images are stored securely in the system.\n- There is no edit function — if details were entered incorrectly, contact your administrator.",
  'scan-new-vin': "# Scan New VIN\n\nUse this to register a new vehicle in the system by photographing its VIN plate and entering the registration.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. Tap **Scan New VIN** from the home screen (Admin section).\n2. Point the camera at the VIN plate on the vehicle and tap **Capture Photo**.\n3. Review the image. Tap **Retake** if it is unclear, or proceed to the next step.\n4. Enter the vehicle's **Registration Plate** (e.g. ABC123).\n5. Tap **Save Vehicle** to submit.\n6. A green \"Vehicle recorded\" message confirms it was saved.\n\n## Where to find the VIN plate\n\n- Dashboard (visible through the windscreen on the driver's side)\n- Driver's door jamb sticker\n- Engine bay\n- On the compliance plate\n\n## Notes\n\n- The VIN photo and registration are sent to the workshop management system via n8n.\n- If the camera does not start, tap **Open Camera** to use the device's standard camera app instead.\n- A clear, well-lit photo of the VIN is important — avoid glare and shadows.",
